# Local conda environment name for THIS forge working copy.
#
# Copy this file to `.conda_env_name` (same directory) and set a unique
# name so this clone gets its own conda env — enabling parallel forge
# development across several clones (e.g. dev-0, dev-1, dev-2), each
# isolated in its own environment.
#
#   cp .conda_env_name.example .conda_env_name
#   # edit .conda_env_name, then run:
#   ./dev/setup.sh
#
# Rules:
#   - Use letters, digits, and underscores ONLY. NO DASHES — conda reads a
#     leading dash as a flag, and dashed env names break activation.
#   - Make it unique per clone (e.g. forge_dev0, forge_dev1, forge_exp).
#
# Precedence: $CONDA_ENV_NAME env var > this file > default "forge".
# If `.conda_env_name` does not exist, ./dev/setup.sh uses: forge
#
# Uncomment and edit the line below, then save this file as `.conda_env_name`:
# forge_dev0
